#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:648
msgid "Checkerboard"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:649
msgid "|Toonz71_417|"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:651
msgid ""
"Creates in the selected column a layer with a checkerboard defined by two"
" Colors, and a grid Size."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:653
msgid ""
"The grid size can also be set by using a square gadget with a handle in "
"the work area (see  :ref:`Using FX Gadgets <using_fx_gadgets>`  )."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:658
msgid "Color Card"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:659
msgid "|Toonz71_418|"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:661
msgid ""
"Creates in the selected column a layer of the set Color. It can be used, "
"for example, as a background color or to create a colorize effect by "
"applying it combined with a multiply effect."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:666
msgid "Kaleido"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:667
msgid "|Toonz71_419|"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:669
msgid "Repeats the Source generating a kaleidoscopic effect."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:671
msgid ""
"The center of the effect can be defined interactively, moving the small "
"red cross widget in the preview area, or writing the desired values in "
"the X and Y text fields."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:673
msgid ""
"The angle of reflection, and the number of iterations can be set in the "
"appropriate input text fields (Angle and Count)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:678
msgid "Tile"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:679
msgid "|Toonz71_420|"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:681
msgid ""
"Repeats the Source content in order to define a larger image: the Tile "
"mode forms a pattern that completely fills the camera shot, the Tile "
"Horizontally repeats the source content horizontally; the Tile Vertically"
" repeats the source content vertically."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:683
msgid ""
"The Mirror Horizontally and Mirror Vertically options repeat the tiles by"
" flipping them respectively in the horizontal and vertical directions; If"
" both the options are activated, tiles will be mirrored in both "
"directions."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:685
msgid ""
"The Margin value sets the size of a margin around each tile, with "
"positive values adding some space around the tiles, and negative values "
"collapsing them."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:690
#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:692
msgid "Blur"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:693
msgid "|Toonz71_421|"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:695
msgid ""
"Softens the Source content, creating an out of focus effect, according to"
" a specific Intensity."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:700
msgid "Directional Blur"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:701
msgid "|Toonz71_422|"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:703
msgid ""
"Blurs the Source content according to a specific Intensity along a "
"specific direction defined by the Angle."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:705
msgid ""
"The Bidirectional option applies the blur also on the other side of the "
"direction."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:707
msgid ""
"The intensity and the angle can also be set by using an arrow gadget with"
" a handle in the work area (see  :ref:`Using FX Gadgets "
"<using_fx_gadgets>`  )."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:709
msgid ""
"The directional blur does not depend on the movement and the speed of the"
" column to which it is applied."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:714
msgid "Local Blur"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:715
msgid "|Toonz71_423|"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:717
msgid ""
"Blurs the Source content according to the brightness value of the node "
"content connected to the Reference input handle. The Intensity value "
"amplifies uniformly the blur given by the Reference node content."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:722
msgid "Motion Blur"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:723
msgid ""
"Creates a motion-blur effect, according to the movement of the Source "
"content in the previous and current frame. The movement has to be defined"
" by an animated column, pegbar or table: the higher the speed, the more "
"visible the effect."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:725
msgid ""
"If the movement is constant between consecutive frames, you can increase "
"or decrease the Intensity to have a more or less visible effect. If there"
" is no movement between the previous and the current frame, no motion "
"blur will be visible even though you may have set a high Intensity."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:727
msgid ""
"No result will be visible if the motion blur is applied to a column that "
"always stands in the same position while the content is a level where the"
" movement is drawn."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:732
msgid "Radial Blur"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:733
msgid "|Toonz71_424|"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:735
msgid ""
"Blurs along radial lines whose origin is the set Center, defined by "
"horizontal (X) and vertical (Y) coordinates, starting from an unaffected "
"inner area defined by the Radius."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:737
#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:747
msgid ""
"The center and the radius can be also set by using a point and a circle "
"gadget with a handle in the work area (see  :ref:`Using FX Gadgets "
"<using_fx_gadgets>`  ); the center can be set in the FX Settings preview "
"as well."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:742
msgid "Spin Blur"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:743
msgid "|Toonz71_425|"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:745
msgid ""
"Blurs along concentric circular lines as if the Source content turns "
"around the set Center, defined by horizontal (X) and vertical (Y) "
"coordinates, starting from an unaffected inner area defined by the "
"Radius."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:752
msgid "Distort"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:756
msgid "Free Distort"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:757
msgid "|Toonz71_426|"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:759
msgid ""
"Distorts the Source content according to the position of four points, "
"defined by horizontal (X) and vertical (Y) coordinates. For each point "
"you can set the actual position and its origin, to determine which "
"feature of the image will be distorted to the new position."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:761
msgid ""
"The Mode option menu lets you set the way the distortion is applied: "
"Bilinear distorts the images according to the four points end positions, "
"and Perspective forces the distortion to fit a perspective projection "
"plane."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:763
msgid ""
"To better set the origin position for each point, you can use the "
"Deactivate option that lets you see the image without distortion."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:765
msgid ""
"The position of the four points and their origins can be also set by "
"using arrow gadgets with handles at the ends in the work area (see  "
":ref:`Using FX Gadgets <using_fx_gadgets>`  ) and in the FX Settings "
"preview as well."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:770
msgid "Linear Wave"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:771
msgid "|Toonz71_427|"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:773
msgid ""
"Distorts the Source content creating a wave effect that uses an "
"automatically generated displacement map image. The Quantity value sets "
"the number of waves; the Period sets the distance between waves; the "
"Cycle shifts distortion in the wave direction."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:775
msgid ""
"You can also add a Distortion Wave on the main linear waves: the "
"Amplitude sets the intensity of the distortion; the Frequency sets the "
"number of waves creating the distortion; the Phase shifts the distorting "
"waves."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:777
msgid "A rotation for the whole wave effect can be set by using the Angle value."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:779
#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:807
#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:821
msgid ""
"The amount of distortion is controlled by the Intensity value; the  of "
"the distortion, by the Size of the displacement map grid; the sharpen "
"option allows you to decrease the blur on the final result."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:784
msgid "Perlin Noise"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:785
msgid "|Toonz71_428|"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:787
msgid ""
"Distorts the Source content by using a computer-generated displacement "
"map image whose type can be chosen between Clouds and Marble/Wood."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:789
msgid ""
"The amount of distortion is controlled by the Intensity value; the , by "
"the Size of the displacement map grid. The Horizontal and Vertical "
"Offset, and the Evolution stage of the displacement map image can be "
"controlled as well; by setting the variation of these values between two "
"keys, you can set how much the displacement map moves and changes during "
"the animation."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:791
msgid ""
"The Alpha option adds also a transparency displacement to fully-opaque "
"images."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:793
msgid ""
"The horizontal and vertical offset can also be set by using a point "
"gadget in the work area (see  :ref:`Using FX Gadgets <using_fx_gadgets>`"
"  )."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:798
msgid "Random Wave"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:799
msgid "|Toonz71_429|"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:801
msgid ""
"Distorts the Source content creating a random wave effect that uses an "
"automatically generated displacement map image. It can be used, for "
"instance, to create a reflection on a water surface, or an underwater "
"view."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:803
#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1547
msgid ""
"The stage of the displacement map image can be controlled by using the "
"Evolution value; by setting the variation of this value between two keys,"
" you set how much the displacement map image changes during the "
"animation."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:805
msgid ""
"The position of the displacement map image can be shifted along the "
"Horizontal and the Vertical axis. By setting the variation of this value "
"between two keys, the distortion effect can be animated in any direction."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:809
msgid ""
"The position along the horizontal and vertical axis can also be set by "
"using a point gadget in the work area (see  :ref:`Using FX Gadgets "
"<using_fx_gadgets>`  )."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:814
msgid "Ripple"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:815
msgid "|Toonz71_430|"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:817
msgid ""
"Distorts the Source content creating a circular wave effect that uses an "
"automatically generated displacement map image. The Quantity value sets "
"the number of ripples; the Period value sets the distance between "
"ripples; the Cycle shifts the ripple distortion, with increasing values "
"expanding the ripples, and decreasing values collapsing them."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:819
msgid ""
"The Center of the circular waves can be set with a Horizontal and "
"Vertical value; circular waves can be scaled in the Horizontal and "
"Vertical directions, and rotated according to a set Angle."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:823
msgid ""
"The center and the period can be also set by using a point and a circle "
"gadget with a handle in the work area (see  :ref:`Using FX Gadgets "
"<using_fx_gadgets>`  ); the center can be set in the FX Settings preview "
"as well."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:828
msgid "Warp"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:829
msgid "|Toonz71_431|"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:831
msgid ""
"Distorts the Source content according to the brightness variation of the "
"node content connected to the Warper input handle, that is used as a "
"displacement map image affecting the Source content."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:833
msgid ""
"The amount of distortion is controlled by the Intensity value; the  of "
"the warp, by the Size of the displacement map grid; the sharpen option "
"allows you to decrease the blur on the final result."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:838
msgid "Gradients"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:842
msgid "Diamond Gradient"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:843
msgid "|Toonz71_432|"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:845
msgid ""
"Creates in the selected column a gradient, that goes hyperbolically from "
"the center to the four corners, defined by a color spectrum (see  "
":ref:`Defining Colors and Color Spectrums "
"<defining_colors_and_color_spectrums>`  ) and a Size value."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:847
msgid ""
"The size can also be set by using a circle gadget with a handle in the "
"work area (see  :ref:`Using FX Gadgets <using_fx_gadgets>`  )."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:852
msgid "Four Points Gradient"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:853
msgid "|Toonz71_433|"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:855
msgid ""
"Creates in the selected column a gradient defined by four Colors, defined"
" by Red, Green, Blue and Alpha values, whose source Points can be placed "
"where needed defining horizontal (X) and vertical (Y) coordinates."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:857
msgid ""
"The source points can also be set by using point gadgets in the work area"
" (see  :ref:`Using FX Gadgets <using_fx_gadgets>`  ) and in the FX "
"Settings preview as well."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:862
msgid "Linear Gradient"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:863
msgid "|Toonz71_434|"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:865
msgid ""
"Creates in the selected column a gradual blend between two Colors defined"
" by Red, Green, Blue and Alpha values. The Size controls the area of the "
"gradient between the two colors."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:867
msgid ""
"You can also add a Distortion Wave on the linear gradient: the Amplitude "
"sets the intensity of the distortion; the Frequency sets the number of "
"waves creating the distortion; the Phase shifts the distorting waves."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:869
msgid ""
"The size can also be set by using a gadget with two handles at the ends "
"in the work area (see  :ref:`Using FX Gadgets <using_fx_gadgets>`  )."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:874
msgid "Multi Linear Gradient"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:875
msgid "|Toonz71_435|"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:877
msgid ""
"Creates in the selected column a multi linear gradient defined by a color"
" spectrum (see  :ref:`Defining Colors and Color Spectrums "
"<defining_colors_and_color_spectrums>`  ). The Period value sets the size"
" of a spectrum gradient; the Quantity is the number of times the spectrum"
" is repeated; the Phase shifts the gradient colors."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:879
msgid ""
"You can also add a Wave distortion on the multi linear gradient: the "
"Amplitude sets the intensity of the distortion; the Frequency sets the "
"number of waves creating the distortion; the Phase shifts the distorting "
"waves."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:881
msgid ""
"The period can also be set by using a gadget with two handles at the ends"
" in the work area (see  :ref:`Using FX Gadgets <using_fx_gadgets>`  )"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:886
msgid "Multi Radial Gradient"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:887
msgid "|Toonz71_436|"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:889
msgid ""
"Creates in the selected column a multi radial gradient defined by a color"
" spectrum (see  :ref:`Defining Colors and Color Spectrums "
"<defining_colors_and_color_spectrums>`  ). The Period value sets the size"
" of a spectrum gradient; the Quantity is the number of times the spectrum"
" is repeated; the Phase shifts the gradient colors."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:891
msgid ""
"The period can be also set by using a circle gadget with a handle in the "
"work area (see  :ref:`Using FX Gadgets <using_fx_gadgets>`  )."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:896
msgid "Radial Gradient"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:897
msgid "|Toonz71_437|"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:899
msgid ""
"Creates in the selected column a gradual blend between two colors, "
"defined by Red, Green, Blue and Alpha values, shading them in a circular "
"pattern. The Inner Size controls the area where the gradient between the "
"two colors begins; the Outer Size where it ends."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:901
msgid ""
"The inner and outer sizes can be also set by using circle gadgets with a "
"handle in the work area (see  :ref:`Using FX Gadgets <using_fx_gadgets>`"
"  )."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:906
msgid "Spiral"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:907
msgid "|Toonz71_438|"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:909
msgid ""
"Creates in the selected column a spiral pattern gradient defined by a "
"color spectrum (see  :ref:`Defining Colors and Color Spectrums "
"<defining_colors_and_color_spectrums>`  ). The Frequency sets the size "
"and number of the spires; the Phase shifts the gradient colors."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:914
msgid "Square Gradient"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:915
msgid "|Toonz71_439|"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:917
msgid ""
"Creates in the selected column a square gradient, that goes linearly from"
" the center to the four corners, defined by a color spectrum (see  "
":ref:`Defining Colors and Color Spectrums "
"<defining_colors_and_color_spectrums>`  ) and a Size value."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:919
msgid ""
"The size can also be set by using a rotated square gadget with handles in"
" the work area (see  :ref:`Using FX Gadgets <using_fx_gadgets>`  )."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:924
msgid "Image Adjust"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:926
msgid "Adjust Levels"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:927
msgid "|Toonz71_440|"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:929
msgid ""
"Adjusts the highlights and shadows of the Source content by remapping "
"pixels intensity according to the Input and Output levels values for the "
"RGB, Red, Green, Blue and Alpha channels; it also controls the Gamma "
"value for each channel separately."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:931
msgid ""
"For each channel the Input values remaps pixel intensity whose value is "
"equal or lower than the Minimum value, to 0, and those whose value is "
"equal or higher than the Maximum value, to 255. This may be helpful to "
"increase the contrast of an image."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:933
msgid ""
"For each channel the Output values remaps pixel intensity whose value is "
"lower than the Minimum value, to the Minimum value, and those whose value"
" is higher than the Maximum value, to the Maximum value. This may be "
"helpful to decrease the contrast of an image."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:938
msgid "Brightness & Contrast"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:939
msgid "|Toonz71_441|"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:941
msgid "Increases or decreases the brightness and contrast of the Source content."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:946
msgid "Despeckle"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:947
msgid "|Toonz71_442|"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:949
msgid ""
"Elimantes small imperfections (dirt, scratches, stains and similar) of "
"the drawing. The size in pixels of the s that will be retouched can be "
"defined in the Size input text field. The background of the images can be"
" Transparent or White, the choise is available in the Detect On menu."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:951
msgid ""
"In the preview area is possible to check the results to avoid erasing s "
"relevant for the drawing."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:956
msgid "Channel Mixer"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:957
msgid "|Toonz71_443|"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:959
msgid ""
"Swaps the channels of the Source content. For each channel you can set if"
" it remains as it is, or if you want it to have another channel mixed. "
"For example to leave the red channel as it is, Red to Red is 1, the other"
" channels to Red are 0; by setting Green to Red to 0.5 adds half "
"intensity of the green channel to the red one."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:961
msgid ""
"It can be used for example to create a black and white key for an image "
"with the alpha channel, by setting all the values to 0 but the Alpha to "
"Red, Green, Blue and Alpha to 1."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:966
msgid "Curves"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:967
msgid "|Toonz71_444|"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:969
msgid ""
"Adjusts the tonal range of the Source content by remapping pixels "
"intensity according to a tonal curve for the RGB, Red, Green, Blue and "
"Alpha channels."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:971
msgid ""
"The horizontal axis of the graph represents the original brightness "
"levels of the pixels (Input levels); the vertical axis represents the new"
" brightness levels (Output levels)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:973
msgid ""
"The default diagonal line indicates that no pixels are mapped to new "
"values, so all pixels have the same Input and Output values."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:975
msgid ""
"It is possible to use many adjustment points to correct the curve: to add"
" a point, click the curve; to change the curve, use the point direction "
"handles; to delete a point, select it and use the delete shortcut (by "
"default the Delete button)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:977
msgid "The Linear option constrains the curve to a series of straight segments."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:982
msgid "Gamma"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:983
msgid "|Toonz71_445|"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:985
msgid "Changes the gamma value of the Source content."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:990
msgid "Invert"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:991
msgid "|Toonz71_446|"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:993
msgid ""
"Inverts the color values of the Source content, e.g. makes a positive "
"black and white image negative, or a positive one from a scanned black "
"and white negative."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:998
msgid "Multitone"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:999
msgid "|Toonz71_447|"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1001
msgid ""
"Applies to the Source content the colors defined by a color spectrum (see"
"  :ref:`Defining Colors and Color Spectrums "
"<defining_colors_and_color_spectrums>`  ) according to the image "
"brightness. The original image is turned into black and white and the "
"color on the far left of the spectrum will be use for black pixels, the "
"color on the far right for white pixels, and in-between colors for in-"
"between grey pixels."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1006
msgid "RGBA Cut"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1007
msgid "|Toonz71_448|"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1009
msgid ""
"Delimits the Minimum and the Maximum values of the Red, Green, Blue and "
"Alpha components of the Source content. The maximum can be decreased from"
" 255, the original value, to 0, when no red, green, blue or alpha "
"component will be visible. The minimum can be increased from 0, the "
"original value, to 255, when the red, green, blue components will be "
"saturated, and alpha will be fully opaque."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1014
msgid "RGB Fade"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1015
msgid "|Toonz71_449|"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1017
msgid ""
"Fades the Source content toward a color defined by Red, Green and Blue "
"values. The Intensity, expressed as a percentage, ranges from 0 (no fade)"
" to 100 (fade to full color)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1022
msgid "RGBA Scale"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1023
msgid "|Toonz71_450|"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1025
msgid ""
"Changes the percentage of the Red, Green, Blue and Alpha components of "
"the Source content. At 0 there is no red, green, blue or alpha component;"
" at 100 the components have their original value."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1030
msgid "HSV Scale"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1031
msgid "|Toonz71_451|"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1033
msgid ""
"Shifts the Hue, Saturation and Value values of the Source content. Hue "
"ranges from -180 to 180; Saturation and Value from -100 to 100. All the "
"three settings preserve their original value at 0."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1038
msgid "Sharpen"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1039
msgid "|Toonz71_452|"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1041
msgid ""
"Increases the sharpness of the Source content according to a specific "
"Intensity."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1046
msgid "Layer Blending"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1050
msgid "Add"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1051
msgid "|Toonz71_453|"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1053
msgid ""
"Adds the red, green and blue values of the Up node content to the Down "
"one, pixel by pixel."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1055
msgid ""
"If no Down node is defined, the adding operation is applied to all the "
"images underlaying the Up node content according to the xsheet layering "
"order."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1057
msgid ""
"The Intensity value expresses the percentage of values used in the "
"addition; a negative value defines a subtraction instead of an addition."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1062
msgid "Color Burn"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1063
msgid "|Toonz71_454|"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1065
msgid ""
"Darkens the pixel colors of the Down node content in order to reflect the"
" color of the Up node content. The white in the Up node content does not "
"affect the result."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1067
msgid ""
"If no Down node is defined, the color burning operation is applied to all"
" the images underlaying the Up node content according to the xsheet "
"layering order."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1072
msgid "Color Dodge"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1073
msgid "|Toonz71_455|"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1075
msgid ""
"Brightens the pixel colors of the Down node content in order to reflect "
"the color of the Up node content. The black in the up node content does "
"not affect the result."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1077
msgid ""
"If no Down node is defined, the color dodging operation is applied to all"
" the images underlaying the Up node content according to the xsheet "
"layering order."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1082
msgid "Cross Dissolve"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1083
msgid "|Toonz71_456|"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1085
msgid ""
"Creates a cross-dissolve between the Up and Down node content. When the "
"Intensity value is 0, only the Down node content is visible; when it is "
"100, only the Up one."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1090
msgid "Darken"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1091
msgid "|Toonz71_457|"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1093
msgid ""
"Compares the pixels color of the Up and Down node content and selects the"
" darker one as the result color. The white in the Up node content does "
"not affect the result; the black gives a black result."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1095
msgid ""
"If only one node is defined, the darkening operation is applied to all "
"the images underlaying its content according to the xsheet layering "
"order."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1100
msgid "Dissolve"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1101
msgid "|Toonz71_458|"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1103
msgid ""
"Eliminates randomly pixels from the Source content according to the set "
"Intensity."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1108
msgid "Lighten"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1109
msgid "|Toonz71_459|"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1111
msgid ""
"Compares the pixels color of the Up and Down node content and selects the"
" lighter one as the result color. The black in the Up node content does "
"not affect the result; the white gives a white result."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1113
msgid ""
"If only one node is defined, the lightening operation is applied to all "
"the images underlaying the connected node according to the xsheet "
"layering order."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1118
msgid "Local Transparency"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1119
msgid "|Toonz71_460|"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1121
msgid ""
"Applies a transparency to the Source content according to the brightness "
"value of the node content connected to the Reference input port."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1123
msgid ""
"The Intensity value amplifies uniformly the transparency given by the "
"Reference node content."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1128
msgid "Multiply"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1129
msgid "|Toonz71_461|"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1131
msgid ""
"Multiplies the red, green, blue and alpha values of the connected noded "
"content."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1133
msgid ""
"The Intensity value expresses the percentage of values used in the "
"multiplication. By activating the Alpha option, also the alpha "
"information is considered."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1135
msgid ""
"If only one node is defined, the multiplying operation is applied to all "
"the images underlaying theupper node content according to the xsheet "
"layering order."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1140
msgid "Over"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1141
msgid "|Toonz71_462|"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1143
msgid ""
"Puts the connected nodes one over the other. Each time a node is "
"connected a new port will be added, this way the overlap of columns can "
"be defined regardless from the xsheet columns order.The columns order is "
"up to bottom, where the column connected on the upper port is over the "
"other ones.This can be used when you need to combine several nodes in a "
"single one, for example to mask several columns with the same mask."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1148
msgid "Premultiply"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1149
msgid "Premultiplies the alpha channel of the Source node content."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1151
msgid ""
"Full-color images which have a meaningful alpha channel come in two "
"types: premultiplied or not. A non-premultiplied image can be recognized "
"when it is loaded in Toonz because its edge, where there is a complete "
"transparence on one side and opacity on the other, is not smooth, but "
"displays a solid halo. With the premultiply effect it is possible to "
"transform the image alpha-channel so that it is correctly read by Toonz."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1153
msgid ""
"Full-color images can also be premultiplied by using a Level Settings "
"option, or processed permanently in the browser, so that there is no need"
" to apply the effect in the schematic (see  :ref:`Editing Level Settings "
"<editing_level_settings>`  and  :ref:`Using the File Browser "
"<using_the_file_browser>`  )."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1158
msgid "Screen"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1159
msgid "|Toonz71_463|"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1161
msgid ""
"Combines by multiplying the inverse of the pixels color of the Up and "
"Down node content, giving a result color that is lighter than both Up and"
" Down node pixels, except when one of them equals 0. The black in the Up "
"node content does not affect the result; the white gives a white result."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1163
msgid ""
"If no Down node is defined, the screening operation is applied to all the"
" images underlaying the Up node content according to the xsheet layering "
"order."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1168
msgid "Subtract"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1169
msgid "|Toonz71_464|"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1171
msgid ""
"Subtracts the red, green and blue values of the Up node content from the "
"Down one, pixel by pixel. By activating the Alpha option, also the alpha "
"information is considered."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1173
msgid ""
"If only one node is defined, the screening operation is applied to all "
"the images underlaying connected node content according to the xsheet "
"layering order."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1178
msgid "Transparency"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1179
msgid "|Toonz71_465|"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1181
msgid ""
"Sets the transparency of the Source content. The Intensity, expressed as "
"a percentage, ranges from 0, fully opaque, to 100, fully transparent."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1183
msgid ""
"In the FXs that accept multiple input nodes it is possible to change the "
"stacking order of the input nodes by clicking and dragging in ports area."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1188
msgid "Light"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1192
msgid "Backlit"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1193
msgid "|Toonz71_466|"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1195
msgid ""
"Creates a backlit effect, using the Light node content as a light source "
"affecting the Source node content. The light node content can be also "
"faded to a Color defined by Red, Green and Blue values, according to the "
"set Intensity."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1200
msgid "Body Highlight"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1201
msgid "|Toonz71_467|"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1203
msgid ""
"Creates a highlighted area for the Source node content, according to its "
"alpha channel. You can set the Color of the highlight, as well as a "
"Transparency and a Blur value to be applied."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1205
msgid ""
"The shifting of the highlighted area is defined by horizontal (X) and "
"vertical (Y) Offset values, that can also be interactively set in the "
"preview of the FX Settings window, where the offset center is displayed "
"with a cross."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1207
msgid "Enabling the Invert option the effected areas will be toggled."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1209
msgid ""
"The effect can be used to create a body shadow as well, by defining a "
"black color for the highlight."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1214
msgid "Cast Shadow"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1215
msgid "|Toonz71_468|"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1217
msgid ""
"Turns the Source content into a shadow that can be distorted and faded to"
" a color with a variable transparency and blur."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1219
msgid ""
"The distortion can be done like in the Free Distort effect (see  "
":ref:`Free Distort <free_distort>`  ). The fade Color can be defined by "
"Red, Green and Blue values and an Intensity can be set. A different Blur "
"and Transparency value can be set for the top and the bottom part of the "
"Source content, in order to have a more realistic shadow."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1224
msgid "Glow"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1225
msgid "|Toonz71_469|"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1227
msgid ""
"Creates a glowing effect, using the Light node content as a light glowing"
" on the node content connected to the Source input port. The Blur and "
"Brightness of the glowing can be set; the Light node content can be also "
"faded to a color defined by Red, Green and Blue values, according to the "
"set Intensity."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1229
msgid ""
"If no Source node is defined, the glowing is applied to all the images "
"underlaying the Light node content according to the xsheet layering "
"order."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1234
msgid "Light Spot"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1235
msgid "|Toonz71_470|"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1237
msgid ""
"Creates in the selected column a light spot whose size and color can be "
"set respectively with the Width and Height values, and the Reg, Green, "
"Blue and Alpha values. The Softness sets the light diffusion in the area "
"outside the spot."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1239
msgid ""
"The width and height can be also set by using a box gadget with handles "
"in the work area (see  :ref:`Using FX Gadgets <using_fx_gadgets>`  )."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1244
msgid "Raylit"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1245
msgid "|Toonz71_471|"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1247
msgid ""
"Places a source of light behind the Source node content, casting rays of "
"light outside or inside the image outline."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1249
#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1267
msgid ""
"The light source position is defined by horizontal (X) and vertical (Y) "
"coordinates. By changing the light source position you change the way "
"rays are cast along the image outline; by changing the Distance value you"
" can make the light source approach to or go away from the image."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1251
msgid ""
"Properties of the light can be set by defining the Intensity, the Color, "
"that is set by Red, Green, Blue and Alpha values, the Decay, that is the "
"decrease of the light intensity according to its distance from the image,"
" and the Smoothness, that determines how sharp the rays are along the "
"image outline."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1253
msgid ""
"The Invert option switches the casting of rays of light from the outside "
"of the image to the inside."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1255
msgid ""
"The center can be also set by using a point gadget in the work area (see"
"  :ref:`Using FX Gadgets <using_fx_gadgets>`  ) and in the FX Settings "
"preview."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1257
msgid ""
"The Source node content needs to have a significant alpha channel in "
"order to have an effective result."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1262
msgid "Color Raylit"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1263
msgid "|Toonz71_472|"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1265
msgid ""
"Places a source of light behind the Source node content, casting rays of "
"light outside the image outline."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1269
msgid "The colours of the rays are calculated from the original drawing colours."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1271
msgid ""
"Properties of the light can be set by defining the Intensity, the Decay, "
"that is the decrease of the light intensity according to its distance "
"from the image, and the Smoothness, that determines how sharp the rays "
"are along the image outline."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1273
msgid ""
"The Keep image check-box determines if the original drawing is rendered "
"in the output or not."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1278
msgid "Target Spot"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1279
msgid "|Toonz71_473|"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1281
msgid ""
"Creates in the selected column a light spot whose size and color can be "
"set respectively with the Width and Height values, and the Red, Green, "
"Blue and Alpha values. The direction of the spot can be set by defining "
"the Distance of the light from the table and the Angle between the light "
"spot direction and the table. The Decay, that is the decrease of the "
"light intensity according to the distance from table, can be controlled "
"as well."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1286
msgid "Matte"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1290
msgid "Erode/Dilate"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1291
msgid "|Toonz71_474|"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1293
msgid ""
"Morphologically erodes or dilates the alpha channel of the connected node"
" by the specified value, where positive values correspond to dilations "
"and negative ones to erosion."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1298
msgid "HSV Key"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1299
msgid "|Toonz71_475|"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1301
msgid ""
"The Type parameter specifies the filter shape to be applied, the square "
"filter being faster than the circular. Key"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1303
msgid ""
"Defines a chroma key for the Source content using the set Hue, Saturation"
" and Value values. You can set the range for each value by using the "
"related Range slider. The selection can be inverted using the Invert "
"button."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1308
msgid "Matte In"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1309
msgid "|Toonz71_476|"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1311
msgid ""
"Makes the Source content visible only inside the opaque areas of the node"
" content connected to the Matte input port."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1316
msgid "Matte Out"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1317
msgid "|Toonz71_477|"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1319
msgid ""
"Makes the source content visible only outside the opaque areas of the "
"node content connected to the Matte input port."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1324
msgid "RGB Key"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1325
msgid "|Toonz71_478|"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1327
msgid ""
"Defines a chroma key for the Source content using the set Red, Green and "
"Blue values. You can set the range for each value by using the related "
"Range slider. The selection can be inverted using the Invert button."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1332
msgid "Visible Matte In"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1333
msgid "|Toonz71_479|"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1335
msgid ""
"Makes the Up node content visible only inside the opaque areas of the "
"node content connected to the Down input port, keeping the Down node "
"still visible."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1340
#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1342
msgid "Noise"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1343
msgid "|Toonz71_480|"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1345
msgid ""
"Adds a noise effect to the Source content according to the set Intensity."
" You can decide which noise component among Red, Green and Blue you want "
"to activate, and if the result has to be in Black and White."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1350
msgid "Salt & Pepper Noise"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1351
msgid "|Toonz71_481|"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1353
msgid ""
"Adds a black and white noise effect to the Source content according to "
"the set Intensity."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1356
msgid "Render"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1360
msgid "Clouds"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1361
msgid "|Toonz71_482|"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1363
msgid ""
"Creates in the selected column a fractal image whose type can be chosen "
"between Clouds and Marble/Wood. The Size affect the grid used for "
"generating the fractal image; a color spectrum defines the used colors "
"(see  :ref:`Defining Colors and Color Spectrums "
"<defining_colors_and_color_spectrums>`  )."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1365
msgid ""
"Increasing the Minimum value shifts the color spectrum to the right, and "
"consequently more pixels will be colored as the color defined at the far "
"left of the spectrum. Decreasing the Maximum value shifts the color "
"spectrum to the left, and consequently more pixels will be colored as the"
" color defined at the far right of the spectrum."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1367
msgid ""
"The Evolution stage of the fractal image can be controlled as well; by "
"setting the variation of this value between two keys, you set how much "
"the fractal image changes during the animation."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1372
msgid "Particles"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1373
msgid "See  :ref:`Using the Particles Effect <using_the_particles_effect>` ."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1378
msgid "Stylize"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1382
msgid "Color Emboss"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1383
msgid "|Toonz71_483|"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1385
msgid ""
"Traces the edges of the Source content with a combination of highlights "
"and shadows. You can set the Intensity of the effect, and the Distance "
"and Direction of the light that create the emboss effect. The Radius sets"
" the depth of the embossing."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1387
msgid ""
"By connecting a node to the Controller port, the Source content will be "
"embossed according to the Controller node content."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1392
msgid "Emboss"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1393
msgid "|Toonz71_484|"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1395
msgid ""
"Turns the Source content to grey areas and traces its edges with a "
"combination of highlights and shadows. You can set the Intensity of the "
"effect, and the Distance and Direction of the light that create the "
"emboss effect. The Radius sets the depth of the embossing."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1400
msgid "Mosaic"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1401
msgid "|Toonz71_485|"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1403
msgid ""
"Turns the Source content in a series of tiles according to the specified "
"Size and Distance. The color and transparency of the tiles are sampled "
"from the source content."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1405
msgid ""
"A Background Color can be set, and will be visible around the tiles. The "
"tile shape can be chosen between Square and Round."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1410
msgid "Posterize"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1411
msgid "|Toonz71_486|"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1413
msgid ""
"Converts the Source content into a number of shades according to the set "
"number of Levels. The shades depends on the brightness values of the "
"source content and the levels are intended for each channel; for example,"
" two levels produces six colors: two for the red, two for the green, and "
"two for the blue."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1418
msgid "Solarize"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1419
msgid "|Toonz71_487|"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1421
msgid ""
"Blends a negative and a positive version of the Source content, as if "
"exposing a photographic print briefly to light during development. You "
"can set the Intensity of the effect and control the Peak Edge, that is "
"the amount of positive and negative image that is used in the blend."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1426
msgid "Toonz Level"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1427
msgid ""
"The Toonz Level special FX can be applied only to Smart Raster and vector"
" levels (TLV and PLI files). They usually affect the drawings they are "
"applied to according to style indexes. Style indexes can be retrieved in "
"the palette after the # symbol in the style tooltip, or in the bottom "
"right corner of the style in large thumbnails mode."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1429
msgid ""
"Index numbers can be specified in the related text field. They have to be"
" separated by a comma; to define a range of indexes, you can type the "
"first and the last separated by a dash (e.g. 4-7 will refer to indexes 4,"
" 5, 6 and 7). To select all indexes, type ``all`` ; to select no index, "
"type ``none`` ."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1431
msgid ""
"Toonz Level special FX have to be always applied first when a series of "
"special FX are applied to an animation level, as they work only on Toonz "
"raster or vector levels that have not been transformed by other effects. "
"However two or more Toonz Level special FX can be applied to the same "
"animation level."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1436
msgid "Art Contour"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1437
msgid "|Toonz71_488|"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1439
msgid ""
"Creates in the Source content a pattern, by repeating the Controller node"
" content, along lines painted with styles whose indexes are specified in "
"the Color Indexes text field. It can be used for example to create "
"scattered brush, or hair and fur effects along drawing lines."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1441
msgid ""
"The Keep Color option assigns the color of the line to the applied "
"pattern; while the Keep Contour option retains the drawing line that will"
" be visible beneath the pattern."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1443
msgid ""
"The way the contents of the Controller node create the pattern depends on"
" the Pattern settings."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1445
msgid ""
"The Density sets the amount of pattern to be applied along the line. By "
"setting the Density to 0, you can specify a Minimum and Maximum Distance "
"between two subsequent images applied as pattern on the line."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1447
msgid ""
"The Size sets the Minimum and Maximum resizing percentage applied to the "
"images used as the pattern; the value 100 is the original size of the "
"images."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1449
msgid ""
"The Orientation sets the Minimum and Maximum rotation angle for the "
"images used as the pattern, according to the line direction; the value 0 "
"display the images perpendicular to the line direction. If the Absolute "
"Orientation option is used, the orientation values do not depend on the "
"direction of the lines: the value 0 is the original images orientation."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1454
msgid "Calligraphic Line"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1455
msgid "|Toonz71_489|"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1457
msgid ""
"Changes in the Source content the thickness of the drawing lines painted "
"with styles whose indexes are specified in the Color Indexes text field."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1459
#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1493
msgid ""
"You can specify the Thickness increase and how it is applied, as a "
"percentage, to the different line directions Horizontal, Vertical, Up "
"Diagonal, Down Diagonal."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1461
msgid ""
"The Smoothness sets the smoothness of the passage between sections of the"
" lines affected by the effect, and those not affected; while the Noise "
"sets the regularity of the edge of the line."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1466
msgid "Color Blending"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1467
msgid "|Toonz71_490|"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1469
msgid ""
"Blends in the Source content lines and areas painted with styles whose "
"indexes are specified in the Color Indexes text field. It can be used for"
" example to blend shadow and highlight areas with the plain colored area,"
" or to create gradients of colors."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1471
msgid ""
"The Intensity sets how wide the blended area between the selected colors "
"will be; while the Smoothness sets how smooth the dithering between "
"blended colors is."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1473
msgid ""
"The No Blending over Other Colors option stops the blending as soon as a "
"line, or an area, whose index is not included in the selection, is "
"detected; if deactivated, the blending between selected colors continues "
"under excluded lines and areas."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1478
msgid "External Palette"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1479
msgid "|Toonz71_491|"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1481
msgid ""
"Applies to the Source content the palette node connected to the Palette "
"input port; if a column node is connected to the Palette input port, the "
"palette related to its content will be considered."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1483
msgid ""
"The original styles of the Tahoma Levels contained in the source node are "
"replaced with those of the levels contained in the palette node according"
" to their style indexes."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1488
msgid "Outline"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1489
msgid "|Toonz71_492|"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1491
msgid ""
"Changes in the Source content the thickness of the drawing external "
"outline."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1495
msgid ""
"The Smoothness sets the smoothness of the passage between sections of the"
" lines affected by the effect, and those not affected; while the Noise "
"sets the regularity of the edge of the outline."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1500
msgid "Palette Filter"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1501
msgid "|Toonz71_493|"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1503
msgid ""
"Filters the styles of the Source content palette according to the indexes"
" specified in the Color Indexes text field."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1505
msgid ""
"The Apply To option menu lets you choose if you want to affect Lines & "
"Area, only Lines or only Areas, even if painted with the same styles; the"
" Action option menu lets you choose if you want to keep or remove the "
"specified styles."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1510
msgid "Pinned Texture"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1511
msgid "|Toonz71_494|"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1513
msgid ""
"Distorts the Texture node content and applies it to the Source content "
"areas that are painted with styles whose indexes are specified in the "
"Color Indexes text field."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1515
msgid ""
"The distortion can be done like in the Free Distort effect (see  "
":ref:`Free Distort <free_distort>`  ) and the texture can be applied like"
" in the Texture effect (see below)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1520
msgid "Texture"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1521
msgid "|Toonz71_495|"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1523
msgid ""
"Applies the Texture node content to the Source content lines and areas "
"that are painted with styles whose indexes are specified in the Color "
"Indexes text field."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1525
msgid ""
"As the texture node content can be animated as you like, this effect "
"allows you to generate animated texture as well."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1527
msgid ""
"The Action option menu lets you choose if you want to apply the texture "
"to the specified styles (Keep) or to apply it to all styles except for "
"the specified ones (Delete)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1529
msgid ""
"The Mode option menu lets you set how the texture node content will be "
"applied: Texture uses the texture to replace selected styles; Pattern "
"preserves the original colors but varies them according to the texture "
"brightness; Add, Subtract, Multiply, Lighten and Darken defines the way "
"the texture is applied to the original colors (see  :ref:`Layer Blending "
"<layer_blending>`  ). In case the Add, subtract or Multiply mode are "
"selected, you can also set the Value of the effect."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1531
msgid ""
"To repeat the texture image and tile it to create a larger texture, you "
"can apply the Tile effect to the texture column before linking it to the "
"Texture node (see  :ref:`Tile <tile>`  )."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1536
msgid "Shaders"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1537
msgid ""
"Toonz enables support for special fxs rendered through hardware-"
"accelereted pixelshaders. Shaders are simple programs compiled by a "
"graphics processing unit that harness the massively parallel architecture"
" of modern graphics devices to execute with extreme speed. Toonz's shader"
" fxs are written in the OpenGL Shading Language (GLSL), and are located "
"in PROJECTROOT/library/shaders. Refer to the readme.txt file there for "
"further s on editing or creating new shader fxs."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1542
msgid "Caustic"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1543
msgid "|Toonz71_496|"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1545
msgid ""
"Create in the selected column a simulation of the reflection of light on "
"a water surface. Sets the color of the water defining the RGBA values of "
"the Water Color parameter."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1556
msgid "Fireball"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1557
msgid "|Toonz71_497|"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1559
msgid "Create in the selected column a ball of flames erupting from a point."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1561
msgid ""
"A range of colors can be defined setting the RGBA values of color 1 and "
"color 2. The stage of the displacement map image can be controlled by "
"using the Evolution value; by setting the variation of this value between"
" two keys, you set how much the displacement map image changes during the"
" animation."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1568
msgid "Glitter"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1569
msgid "|Toonz71_498|"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1571
msgid ""
"Adds cross-shaped light rays extending from the brightest part of an "
"image."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1573
msgid ""
"Use Threshold to specify the cut-out on the input image's brightest part."
" Higher values will make the fx add lights also to darker image parts, "
"producing more lights. The Brightness specifies the brightness of added "
"light rays; the Radius specify how much the light rays will extend from "
"bright input pixels; the Angle specify the angle of light crosses. A "
"value 0 means that produced light crosses will be axis-aligned. Halo is "
"the amount of light disperion orthogonal to the direction of light rays. "
"Higher values will produce broader rays."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1578
msgid "Star Sky"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1579
msgid "|Toonz71_499|"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1581
msgid ""
"Creates, in the selected column, a simple star field with variable "
"brightness with overlayed clouds. Sets the color of the overlayed clouds "
"defining the RGBA values of the Cloud Color parameter."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1583
msgid ""
"The stage of the stars displacement can be controlled by using the "
"Evolution value; by setting the variation of this value between two keys,"
" you set how much the displacement map image changes during the "
"animation."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1585
msgid "Use the Brightness parameters to define the brightness of the stars."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1592
msgid "Sun Flare"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1593
msgid "|Toonz71_500|"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1595
msgid ""
"Creates, in the selected column, rays of colored light extending from a "
"radial gradient at the center. Sets the color of the sun rays defining "
"the RGBA values of the Cloud Color parameter. The number of rays is "
"defined by the Rays parameter while their brightness is set by the "
"Intensity one. The angle parameter sets the direction of the rays and the"
" Bias parameter define the size of the rays. Use the Sharpness parameter "
"to make the rays sharper or smoother."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1604
msgid "Wavy"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1605
msgid "|Toonz71_501|"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1607
msgid ""
"Creates a simple gradient with a colored 'wavy' pattern in the selected "
"column.The waves colors are definied by setting the RGBA value of the "
"Color and Color 2 parameters. The stage of the displacement map image can"
" be controlled by using the Evolution value; by setting the variation of "
"this value between two keys, you set how much the displacement map image "
"changes during the animation."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1616
msgid "GPU Radial Blur"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1617
msgid "|Toonz71_502|"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1619
msgid ""
"Blurs along radial lines whose origin is the set Center, defined by "
"horizontal (X) and vertical (Y) coordinates, starting from an unaffected "
"inner area defined by the Safe Radius. The Blur Factor parameter sets the"
" amount of blur."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1624
msgid "GPU Spin Blur"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1625
msgid "|Toonz71_503|"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/applying_special_fx.rst:1627
msgid ""
"Blurs along concentric circular lines as if the Source content turns "
"around the set Center, defined by horizontal (X) and vertical (Y) "
"coordinates, starting from an unaffected inner area defined by the Safe "
"Radius. The Blur parameter sets the amount of blur."
msgstr ""

